{"title":"Macworld Podcast: Your hot takes on the Apple Vision Pro, thin MacBooks, iPads being iPads, and more","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2383855/macworld-podcast-your-hot-takes-on-the-apple-vision-pro-thin-macbooks-ipads-being-ipads-and-more.html","date":1720685700000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>On this week‚Äôs episode of the Macworld Podcast it‚Äôs all about your hot takes! You have thoughts about the world of Apple, and we to talk about them on the show! It‚Äôs a good one, so tune in!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 892 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/karen_haslam\" target=\"_blank\">Karen Haslam</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/david.price\" target=\"_blank\">David Price</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Listen to episode 892 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\t\t\n\t\t<div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t\n\t\t\t</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Listen to episode 892 on Spotify</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<h2>Hot takes from social media</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Macworld‚Äôs David Price recently wrote, ‚Äú<a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2369096/the-vision-pro-is-a-flop-just-like-the-ipod.html\" target=\"_blank\">Apple Vision Pro is a flop‚Ä¶ just like the iPod</a>.‚Äù And a couple of people took issue with the headline that‚Äìin our opinion‚Äìwasn‚Äôt understood completely.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Clearly you don‚Äôt know what you‚Äôre talking about. By all accounts is a success and will be in the future. The Mac, iPhone, iPad, AirPods, Apple Watch and more were all called failures</p>‚Äî lucas (@lucas3746) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/lucas3746/status/1805540868964634977?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 25, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>The difference?  The market is already flooded with VR/AR headsets for way cheaper.  Also of note, it‚Äôs a super niche market.  Everyone listens to music, but not everyone cares to play with VR, and at the end of the day, that‚Äôs what it is; a toy.  Just like the iPad.</p>‚Äî relativemedia ‚Äì Emmy Award Winner (@relativemedia) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/relativemedia/status/1805292926831939887?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 24, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Apple seems to be plowing ahead with the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2369453/ipad-pro-thin-design-iphone-macbook-apple-watch.html\">idea that thinness is its next innovation</a>. But is it really something users are asking for?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Who says things like that? Who? Us Macbook users are spoilt whichever model from recent years you have. You should be enjoying using your beautiful, powerful and capable machine not. \"Darling, why can't you sleep?\" \"Because my Macbook Pro is simply not thin enough, ahhhhh!\" ü§°</p>‚Äî Mistahummmus (@mistahummmus) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mistahummmus/status/1806070061049815483?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 26, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I‚Äôd rather have more battery and better thermals</p>‚Äî Caramel Craft (@caramel_craft) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/caramel_craft/status/1803282827921785228?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 19, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And finally, it doesn‚Äôt seem like <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2361678/wwdc-ipados-18-what-to-do-with-ipad.html\">Apple has any idea of what to do with the iPad</a>. But some people think we‚Äôre overthinking it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>tablets should be tablets.<br /><br />if you want a Mac, buy a Mac.  if i buy an iPad, i want it to be an iPad.<br /><br />not rocket science.</p>‚Äî Will Faix (@WilliamFaix) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/WilliamFaix/status/1803094483682136404?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 18, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I believe it is people who want a Mac but think they want an iPad who are the one that still have no idea what to do with the iPad. I and many others use the iPad for productivity and it works out great. It needs some improvements, but this take is wrong. <a href=\"https://t.co/BcFMxUpXFE\">https://t.co/BcFMxUpXFE</a></p>‚Äî Alex (@MacFan2410) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/MacFan2410/status/1802906026770907231?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 18, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Wait, who wrote this? I thought the outbreak of drooling fanboy babble had consumed the whole staff there!</p>‚Äî Rob Williams (@codeslubber) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/codeslubber/status/1802842778923319402?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 17, 2024</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Subscribe to the Macworld Podcast</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can subscribe to the Macworld Podcast‚Äîor leave us a review!‚Äî<a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198\">right here in the Podcasts app</a>. The Macworld Podcast is also <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/show/3uyZkE4tjbwNNrJCLsBUAM?si=OdOljEAYQvC_ewEsMfKzXA\">available on Spotify</a>. Or you can point your favorite podcast-savvy RSS reader at: https://feeds.megaphone.fm/macworld</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find previous episodes, visit <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/opinion/podcast\">Macworld‚Äôs podcast page</a> or our home on <a href=\"https://cms.megaphone.fm/channel/macworld\">MegaPhone</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><a href=\"https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198\"><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge-standard.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/apple-podcasts-badge-standard.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/w